article.headline: Western Kentucky 74, Ky Wesleyan 67
article.story: BOWLING GREEN, Ky. (AP) -- Courtney Lee made four consecutive 3-pointers in less than two minutes during the second half as sluggish Western Kentucky defeated Division II Kentucky Wesleyan 74-67 Tuesday night. Lee made his first 3-pointer with 5:50 to play for the Hilltoppers (20-10), then made 3-point shots on the next three possessions to give Western Kentucky a 66-57 lead with 4:10 left. But the Hilltoppers had to fight back one last challenge from the pesky Panthers (11-14), who moved to within three points at 70-67 on Yannick Murry's shot with 47 seconds to play. Western Kentucky struggled throughout the first half, leading by just 29-24 at halftime, but appeared to be on the verge of blowing the game open by outscoring the Panthers 13-3 to take a 15-point lead at 42-27 with 16:41 to play. Wesleyan got as close as 52-50 on Tim Baker's basket with 7:49 to play before Lee's spurt sparked the Hilltoppers to the win. Lee paced Western Kentucky with 20 points, while Tyrone Brazelton finished with 14. Jeff Fahnbulleh led Kentucky Wesleyan with 19 points. Rodney Edgerson added 16 and Baker 12 for the Panthers.
